The paper focuses on Agile software development methodologies, specifically Scrum, and proposes a metric to measure the quality of the testing process in Scrum. This falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE) and software development (cs.SD). The paper also discusses the process of Scrum, which can be categorized under programming languages (cs.PL) and computer engineering (cs.CE). Additionally, the paper emphasizes the importance of product and process quality, which can be related to human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
